    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6209" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μήν</span></b> : asseverative particle,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">indeed, in truth, verily</span>, cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μά̄ν</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μέν</span> (2).
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μήν</span> regularly stands in combination
          with another particle (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καὶ μήν, ἦ μήν, οὐ
            μήν</span>), or with an imperative like <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄγε</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          1.302</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
